        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 8:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with frequent
lightning along a line extending from 8 miles northeast of Shelby to
10 miles southeast of Forest City, and moving southeast at 5 mph.

Locations to be impacted include...
Shelby, Lawndale, Patterson Springs, Fallston, Polkville, Lattimore,
Waco, Kingstown, Earl, and Belwood.

In addition to intense lightning, very heavy rainfall rates up to 2
inches per hour will be possible in these areas.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent lightning is occurring with these storms. If outdoors, try
to get indoors or into a hard topped vehicle. Otherwise, stay away
from open areas and isolated high objects such as trees. When
indoors, stay away from windows and doors and avoid using wired
electronic devices. Do not take a shower or bath. Try to unplug
unnecessary appliances before the storms approach.</instruction>
